## ğŸš€ Installation
To compile and use **ft_printf** in your projects:
```sh
git clone https://github.com/Tudor-Ursescu/ft_printf.git
cd ft_printf
make
```
This will generate `libftprintf.a`, a static library that can be linked to your projects.

## ğŸ› ï¸ Usage
To use **ft_printf** in your C programs, include the header and link the library:
```c
#include "ft_printf.h"
```
Compile your main with:
```sh
gcc -Wall -Wextra -Werror src/main.c -L. -lftprintf -o output
```

### Example Usage
```c
#include "ft_printf.h"

int main() {
    ft_printf("Hello, %s! You have %d new messages.\n", "User", 5);
    return 0;
}
```

